RECOMMENDED ACTION FOR NEXT GUIDE REVISION
================================================================================

PRIMARY RECOMMENDATION: Revert to qwen2.5:7b-instruct-q4_K_M
--------------------------------------------------------------
The original model used in the guide before the March 2026 update is the correct
choice for this stack. Rationale:

  COMPATIBILITY: qwen2.5:7b has no hybrid thinking architecture. It does not produce
  <think> tokens. Open WebUI's tool-call pipeline handles its responses correctly.
  Tool calls invoke, return, and produce a final answer reliably.

  STACK ALIGNMENT: The entire guide (mcpo config, Wall-E Modelfile system prompt,
  Open WebUI Native tool calling mode, HA Ollama integration) was designed and tested
  with qwen2.5 series models. The March 2026 migration to qwen3 was premature.

  PERFORMANCE: qwen2.5:7b-instruct-q4_K_M runs at 18–22 tok/s on the 780M iGPU.
  This is within the guide's documented target range and delivers 3–5 second voice
  latency for standard commands — exactly the expected behaviour in the summary doc.

  SIZE: ~4.7 GB vs qwen3:8b's ~5.5 GB. The smaller footprint leaves more GTT headroom
  on the iGPU and reduces first-load latency.

  NO THINKING MODE COMPLICATIONS: No /no_think required. No think toggle in Open WebUI.
  No Modelfile workaround needed. The model behaves as a standard instruction-following
  model with clean tool call / tool response / final answer cycles.

SECONDARY RECOMMENDATION: Monitor Qwen3 upstream fixes before re-migration
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Qwen3 has superior benchmark scores and will likely become the correct choice once
the Open WebUI tool-call pipeline issues are resolved. The guide should re-evaluate
migration when the following conditions are met:

  1. open-webui/open-webui #14577 and related issues are closed with a confirmed fix.
  2. Ollama adds native Modelfile support for think=false (tracked in Ollama roadmap).
  3. The Open WebUI "role:tool content:null" malformed message bug (#17135) is resolved.
  4. Verified end-to-end test: memory write + recall across sessions works without
     empty responses or loops on qwen3:8b-q4_K_M + mcpo + Open WebUI :main.

TERTIARY RECOMMENDATION: If keeping Qwen3, document required workarounds
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
If the guide author wishes to keep qwen3:8b as the recommended model despite current
issues, the following must be explicitly documented:

  a) PARAMETER think false does not work — remove from Modelfile example.
  b) think (Ollama) in Open WebUI Advanced Parameters must be set to Default, not Off.
  c) Tool responses after memory/filesystem calls will frequently produce no output.
     Users must regenerate or rephrase. This is a known upstream bug, not misconfiguration.
  d) Infinite tool-call loops are possible. Set Tool Call Auto-Execute Max Count to 5.
  e) Disable Open WebUI built-in Memory for wall-e model to avoid tool disambiguation
     failures.
  f) The /no_think system prompt token works in terminal (ollama run) but is overridden
     by Open WebUI's think API parameter. Terminal and Open WebUI behaviour will differ.

These are not minor caveats — they fundamentally break the memory and filesystem
features that are central to the guide's value proposition.


